SIMPLE: fatness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fatness
<hw>Fat"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or state
of being fat, plump, or full-fed; corpulency; fullness of
flesh.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Their eyes stand out with <qex>fatness</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Ps.
lxxiii. 7.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence; Richness; fertility; fruitfulness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Rich in the <qex>fatness</qex> of her plenteous soil.</q>
<rj><qau>Rowe.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>That which makes fat or fertile.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The clouds drop <qex>fatness</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Philips.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>fatso</ent>⟦br⟧
